+{"id":"asupersync-07w","title":"Meta-testing framework: testing the testing infrastructure","description":"## Purpose
Implement a meta-testing framework that validates the correctness and completeness of Asupersync's testing infrastructure itself. This ensures that oracles, the lab runtime, and test utilities actually catch the bugs they're designed to catch.

## Background from Research
From S2.dev's mad-turmoil approach:
> "We added meta tests that rerun the same seed and compare TRACE-level logs byte-by-byte."

Meta-testing validates that:
1. **Oracles catch violations**: Known-buggy code triggers oracle failures
2. **Determinism holds**: Same seed produces identical traces
3. **Coverage is complete**: All invariants have test coverage
4. **No false positives**: Correct code never triggers oracles

## Design Principles

### Mutation Testing Philosophy
We inject KNOWN bugs (mutations) and verify our oracles DETECT them. If an oracle doesn't catch a mutation, the oracle is incomplete or buggy.

### Self-Referential Validation
The meta-testing framework itself must be tested:
- Does the mutation injection work?
- Do we correctly identify oracle triggers?
- Is the coverage report accurate?

## Implementation

### File Structure
```
src/lab/meta/
├── mod.rs           # Module exports
├── mutation.rs      # Mutation definitions and injection
├── runner.rs        # Meta-test execution engine
├── coverage.rs      # Coverage tracking and reporting
├── chaos.rs         # Chaos testing mode
└── report.rs        # Human/JSON report generation

tests/meta/
├── oracle_mutations.rs    # Mutation tests for each oracle
├── determinism_meta.rs    # Determinism verification
├── coverage_meta.rs       # Coverage completeness tests
└── self_validation.rs     # Tests that test the testing
```

### 1. Mutation Definitions
```rust
// src/lab/meta/mutation.rs

use std::fmt;

/// All possible mutations we can inject to test oracles
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub enum Mutation {
    // =========================================================================
    // Task Lifecycle Mutations (tests: TaskLeak, RegionTree oracles)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Spawn a task but never poll it to completion
    LeakTask,

    /// Allow task to outlive its parent region
    OrphanTask,

    /// Complete a task twice (double-free equivalent)
    DoubleComplete,

    /// Panic inside a task without proper handling
    UnhandledTaskPanic,

    // =========================================================================
    // Obligation Mutations (tests: ObligationLeak oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Create SendPermit but neither commit nor abort
    LeakObligation,

    /// Commit an obligation twice
    DoubleCommit,

    /// Abort an obligation twice
    DoubleAbort,

    /// Commit after already aborting
    CommitAfterAbort,

    /// Abort after already committing
    AbortAfterCommit,

    // =========================================================================
    // Cancellation Mutations (tests: CancellationProtocol oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Ignore cancel request entirely
    IgnoreCancel,

    /// Skip the drain phase
    SkipDrain,

    /// Skip the finalization phase
    SkipFinalize,

    /// Exceed cleanup budget during drain
    DrainBudgetExceeded,

    /// Exceed cleanup budget during finalize
    FinalizeBudgetExceeded,

    // =========================================================================
    // Race Mutations (tests: LoserDrain oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Don't drain the losing branch of a race
    AbandonLoser,

    /// Return wrong winner from race
    WrongWinner,

    /// Allow loser to continue running
    LoserContinues,

    // =========================================================================
    // Region Mutations (tests: Quiescence, RegionTree oracles)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Close region while children still running
    CloseWithActiveChildren,

    /// Close region with unresolved obligations
    CloseWithObligations,

    /// Return handle that escapes region lifetime
    EscapeRegionLifetime,

    /// Access region after close
    UseAfterClose,

    // =========================================================================
    // Determinism Mutations (tests: Determinism oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Use std::collections::HashMap instead of DetHashMap
    UseNonDetHashMap,

    /// Use std::time::Instant instead of virtual time
    UseWallTime,

    /// Use thread_rng() instead of Cx entropy
    UseAmbientRng,

    /// Use std::thread::sleep instead of virtual sleep
    UseRealSleep,

    // =========================================================================
    // Finalizer Mutations (tests: Finalizer oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Register finalizer but don't run it
    SkipFinalizer,

    /// Run finalizer twice
    DoubleFinalizer,

    /// Finalizer panics
    FinalizerPanic,

    /// Finalizer exceeds budget
    FinalizerTimeout,

    // =========================================================================
    // Ambient Authority Mutations (tests: AmbientAuthority oracle)
    // =========================================================================

    /// Spawn task without Cx capability
    SpawnWithoutCapability,

    /// Access time without Cx
    TimeWithoutCapability,

    /// Perform I/O without Cx
    IoWithoutCapability,
}

impl Mutation {
    /// Returns all mutation variants for exhaustive testing
    pub fn all() -> Vec<Mutation> {
        use Mutation::*;
        vec![
            // Task lifecycle
            LeakTask, OrphanTask, DoubleComplete, UnhandledTaskPanic,
            // Obligations
            LeakObligation, DoubleCommit, DoubleAbort, CommitAfterAbort, AbortAfterCommit,
            // Cancellation
            IgnoreCancel, SkipDrain, SkipFinalize, DrainBudgetExceeded, FinalizeBudgetExceeded,
            // Race
            AbandonLoser, WrongWinner, LoserContinues,
            // Region
            CloseWithActiveChildren, CloseWithObligations, EscapeRegionLifetime, UseAfterClose,
            // Determinism
            UseNonDetHashMap, UseWallTime, UseAmbientRng, UseRealSleep,
            // Finalizer
            SkipFinalizer, DoubleFinalizer, FinalizerPanic, FinalizerTimeout,
            // Ambient authority
            SpawnWithoutCapability, TimeWithoutCapability, IoWithoutCapability,
        ]
    }

    /// Returns mutations for a specific category
    pub fn by_category(category: MutationCategory) -> Vec<Mutation> {
        use Mutation::*;
        match category {
            MutationCategory::TaskLifecycle => vec![LeakTask, OrphanTask, DoubleComplete, UnhandledTaskPanic],
            MutationCategory::Obligation => vec![LeakObligation, DoubleCommit, DoubleAbort, CommitAfterAbort, AbortAfterCommit],
            MutationCategory::Cancellation => vec![IgnoreCancel, SkipDrain, SkipFinalize, DrainBudgetExceeded, FinalizeBudgetExceeded],
            MutationCategory::Race => vec![AbandonLoser, WrongWinner, LoserContinues],
            MutationCategory::Region => vec![CloseWithActiveChildren, CloseWithObligations, EscapeRegionLifetime, UseAfterClose],
            MutationCategory::Determinism => vec![UseNonDetHashMap, UseWallTime, UseAmbientRng, UseRealSleep],
            MutationCategory::Finalizer => vec![SkipFinalizer, DoubleFinalizer, FinalizerPanic, FinalizerTimeout],
            MutationCategory::AmbientAuthority => vec![SpawnWithoutCapability, TimeWithoutCapability, IoWithoutCapability],
        }
    }

    /// Which oracle(s) should catch this mutation
    pub fn expected_oracles(&self) -> Vec<Oracle> {
        use Mutation::*;
        use Oracle::*;

        match self {
            LeakTask | OrphanTask => vec![TaskLeak, RegionTree],
            DoubleComplete => vec![TaskLeak],
            UnhandledTaskPanic => vec![TaskLeak],

            LeakObligation => vec![ObligationLeak],
            DoubleCommit | DoubleAbort | CommitAfterAbort | AbortAfterCommit => vec![ObligationLeak],

            IgnoreCancel | SkipDrain | SkipFinalize => vec![CancellationProtocol],
            DrainBudgetExceeded | FinalizeBudgetExceeded => vec![CancellationProtocol, DeadlineMonotone],

            AbandonLoser | WrongWinner | LoserContinues => vec![LoserDrain],

            CloseWithActiveChildren | CloseWithObligations => vec![Quiescence],
            EscapeRegionLifetime | UseAfterClose => vec![RegionTree],

            UseNonDetHashMap | UseWallTime | UseAmbientRng | UseRealSleep => vec![Determinism],

            SkipFinalizer | DoubleFinalizer | FinalizerPanic | FinalizerTimeout => vec![Finalizer],

            SpawnWithoutCapability | TimeWithoutCapability | IoWithoutCapability => vec![AmbientAuthority],
        }
    }

    /// Human-readable description
    pub fn description(&self) -> &'static str {
        use Mutation::*;
        match self {
            LeakTask => "Spawn task but never complete it",
            OrphanTask => "Allow task to outlive parent region",
            DoubleComplete => "Complete a task twice",
            UnhandledTaskPanic => "Panic in task without handling",
            LeakObligation => "Create obligation but never resolve it",
            DoubleCommit => "Commit an obligation twice",
            DoubleAbort => "Abort an obligation twice",
            CommitAfterAbort => "Commit after aborting",
            AbortAfterCommit => "Abort after committing",
            IgnoreCancel => "Ignore cancellation request",
            SkipDrain => "Skip drain phase during cancel",
            SkipFinalize => "Skip finalization phase",
            DrainBudgetExceeded => "Exceed budget during drain",
            FinalizeBudgetExceeded => "Exceed budget during finalize",
            AbandonLoser => "Abandon losing race branch",
            WrongWinner => "Return wrong winner from race",
            LoserContinues => "Let loser continue after race",
            CloseWithActiveChildren => "Close region with active children",
            CloseWithObligations => "Close region with pending obligations",
            EscapeRegionLifetime => "Return handle escaping region",
            UseAfterClose => "Access region after close",
            UseNonDetHashMap => "Use non-deterministic HashMap",
            UseWallTime => "Use wall clock instead of virtual time",
            UseAmbientRng => "Use ambient RNG instead of Cx",
            UseRealSleep => "Use real sleep instead of virtual",
            SkipFinalizer => "Register finalizer but skip running",
            DoubleFinalizer => "Run finalizer twice",
            FinalizerPanic => "Panic inside finalizer",
            FinalizerTimeout => "Exceed budget in finalizer",
            SpawnWithoutCapability => "Spawn without Cx capability",
            TimeWithoutCapability => "Access time without Cx",
            IoWithoutCapability => "Perform I/O without Cx",
        }
    }

    /// Severity level for reporting
    pub fn severity(&self) -> Severity {
        use Mutation::*;
        match self {
            // Critical: Memory safety or correctness
            LeakTask | OrphanTask | DoubleComplete | LeakObligation | 
            AbandonLoser | CloseWithActiveChildren | EscapeRegionLifetime => Severity::Critical,

            // High: Violates core invariants
            DoubleCommit | DoubleAbort | IgnoreCancel | SkipDrain |
            WrongWinner | CloseWithObligations | UseAfterClose => Severity::High,

            // Medium: Violates determinism or protocol
            UseNonDetHashMap | UseWallTime | UseAmbientRng | UseRealSleep |
            SkipFinalize | SkipFinalizer => Severity::Medium,

            // Low: Recoverable or edge cases
            _ => Severity::Low,
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum MutationCategory {
    TaskLifecycle,
    Obligation,
    Cancellation,
    Race,
    Region,
    Determinism,
    Finalizer,
    AmbientAuthority,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord)]
pub enum Severity {
    Low,
    Medium,
    High,
    Critical,
}

impl fmt::Display for Mutation {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "{:?}: {}", self, self.description())
    }
}
